It's important to have the systems and data available, but only for the right people. That's why a lot of time and money are spend in monitoring and redundant systems. When
downtime happens, it is important to mitigate it as much as possible. The term resilience refers to the capacity for a system to recover from a downtime. To measure the
resilience is MTTR (Mean Time To Repair).
-Cost
-Another infrastructure consideration in responsiveness which is how quickly do we get a response.
-Scalability refers for how quickly and easy can we increase the capacity
